(firstQuint)Metacognitive Therapy for Comorbid Insomnia.

 This study is a randomized controlled trial with 50 patients with a psychiatric disorder and insomnia.

 The patients will be randomized into two groups of 25 patients.

 The first group receives meta-cognitive therapy, whereas the second group will be assigned to a waiting list control.

